  "body": "- [ x ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIf `Two.sol` has `import \"One.sol\"` and `One.sol` is edited, executing `truffle compile` will only recompile `One.sol` and not `Two.sol`... though `Two.sol` may need to be recompiled to work correctly.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate two files:\r\n\r\nOne.sol\r\n```\r\ncontract One {}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTwo.sol\r\n```\r\nimport \"One.sol\";\r\ncontract Two{}\r\n```\r\n\r\nExecute `truffle compile`.\r\n\r\nEdit `One.sol` in any manner.\r\n\r\nExecute `truffle compile` again.  Notice, only `One.sol` gets recompiled, though `Two.sol` may require the changes.  (eg, you may have added a function in One.sol that Two.sol wants to use, or changed parameters, etc).\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if `Two.sol` were recompiled, since it imports `One.sol`.  However, this can get quite complex, as recompiling `Two.sol` would entail also recompiling anything that has `import \"Two.sol\"`, and so forth.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nOne `One.sol` is compiled.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: \r\n* Truffle version:\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* node version:\r\n* npm version: \r\n",
